# Images and Performance

Full reference: [design-standards.md](mdc:docs/design-standards.md) section 5.

## Every Image Must Have

- `width` and `height` attributes (prevents CLS layout shift)
- `alt` text (descriptive for content images, empty for decorative)

```tsx
// BAD — missing dimensions and alt
<img src="/assets/product.jpg" />

// GOOD
<img
  src="/assets/product.jpg"
  width={800}
  height={420}
  alt="Range of toroidal transformers in various sizes"
/>
```

## Loading Strategy

| Position | `loading` | `fetchPriority` |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| Above fold (hero, first section) | omit (eager) | `"high"` |
| Below fold | `"lazy"` | omit |
| Decorative/background | `"lazy"` | omit |

## File Size and Format

- Maximum 200KB per image. Current 4-7MB JPGs must be compressed.
- Prefer WebP for photographs, SVG for logos and icons.
- Never commit uncompressed originals to the repo.

## Bundle Size

- Heavy client components: `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`.
- No large library imports in server components.
